INSERT into JourneysHasQuests(3000,30004);
INSERT into Requirements(300041,'Demonstrate your commitment','by actively assisting during four sessions of the Brownie Quest (even better; come to all of them!)
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30004,300041);
INSERT into Requirements(300042,'Do the following:','
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30004,300042);
INSERT into Requirements(300043,'Demonstrate your organizing','skills by preparing the materials and instructions for three Quest activities in advance of their sessions. Each session includes two to three activities; so there is plenty to do to keep each session running smoothly. You can go over the activities with the Quest\'s adult guides and discuss how you can best assist.
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30004,300043);
INSERT into Requirements(300044,'Demonstrate a special skill','\"or talent you have by planning and guiding the Brownies to do one \"\"just for fun\"\" extra activity while they are on the Quest. For example; perhaps you are good at crafts and want to teach the girls to make a gift for themselves or a friend. Or perhaps you are science-minded and can think of a little experiment the Brownies can do during a session. Maybe you can sing or dance or make up funny cheers. You get the idea-add a little of the extra joy you uniquely bring to a Brownie session! Try to make whatever you do tie into the Quest. And remember; the Brownies already have a lot going on to earn their keys-so you\'ll want to keep your little extra short and sweet!\"
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30004,300044);
INSERT into Requirements(300045,'\"While on the Quest','\"the Brownies will be leading their families and communities in \"\"healthy-living\"\" actions like making and enjoying healthy treats or playing a game that gets people up and moving. Take the healthy living even further by doing one of these:  -Bring the fixings for a simple; healthy snack to a session (carrots and low-fat dip; apples and yogurt); assist the girls in \"\"making\"\" the treat; and explain (perhaps on poster board) - in a Brownie-Friendly way - why that snack is better than something else (like_____).  -Teach the brownies to do a simple exercise or stretch that you know and like; and use it as a \"\"quick break\"\" between activities. Offer a short explanation of why it\'s good!  - Bring some music and get everybody moving as the meeting starts or ends - or when an energy boost is needed! Offer a quick explanation of why it\'s good!\" 
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30004,300045);
INSERT into Requirements(300046,'Talk to the adults guiding the Quest','Find out one thing you did during Brownie Quest that was really; really great (a perfect 10!). Then find out one thing that youc an keep in mind-to practice for the next time you team up with younger girls in Girl Scouts.
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30004,300046);
INSERT into Journeys(3001,'BREATHE');
INSERT into Quests(30011,'Aware');
INSERT into JourneysHasQuests(3001,30011);
INSERT into Requirements(300111,'Keep an Air Log','throughout the journey. Record what you see; hear; feel; and smell in the air.
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30011,300111);
INSERT into Requirements(300112,'Identify two experts','who can guide you to greater air awareness (meteorologists; biologists; wind farm or aeronautical engineers; parasailing instructors; astronauts; physicians or other health specialists; fragrance specialists; yoga instructors.)
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30011,300112);
INSERT into Requirements(300113,'Increase your AWAREness','about the issues that impact Earth\'s air. Check out all the air issues throughout Breathe. Take a walk; with some Cadette friends (and of course a trusty adult); around a school; business district; a mall; or other area in search of air issues. Think about trees or think about noise!
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30011,300113);
INSERT into Requirements(300114,'Decide the most important','personal reason you care about Earth\'s air. Write a statement that explains why this reason matters to you and why it should matter to others. Share your AWAREness statement with your sister Cadettes.
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30011,300114);
INSERT into Quests(30012,'Alert');
INSERT into JourneysHasQuests(3001,30012);
INSERT into Requirements(300121,'With your Cadette team','choose an air issue to act on together. Learn as much as you can about it (use experts you\'ve met) and write a statement that explains why it\'s important to educate and inspire others on this issue.
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30012,300121);
INSERT into Requirements(300122,'Decide whom to educate','and inspire--this is your Air Care Team (ACT)! What groups of people would be best to join with you? Principals and teachers? Parents? Your peers? Who can best assist you in moving forward?
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30012,300122);
INSERT into Requirements(300123,'Decide what you will ask','your Air Care Team to do. What call to action will you deliver as you educate and inspire? How will your ACT\'s efforts on this call to action improve your air issue?
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30012,300123);
INSERT into Requirements(300124,'Decide how to reach','your Air Care Team to inspire them to act on your air issue. The medium and method are up to you. The goal is to engage all their senses and create a sustainable effort! Air needs more than just a one-time gathering!
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30012,300124);
INSERT into Requirements(300125,'Educate and inspire!','Give your ACT its call to action. Feel the rewards of influencing others in a lasting way!
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30012,300125);
INSERT into Quests(30013,'Affirm');
INSERT into JourneysHasQuests(3001,30013);
INSERT into Requirements(300131,'Gather proof of progress','or improvement through your efforts to educate and inspire. What is the ACT doing to benefit air?
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30013,300131);
INSERT into Requirements(300132,'Share the impact','with your ACT and maybe even go further. Contact a local media outlet or ask your library for display space.
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30013,300132);
INSERT into Requirements(300133,'Get with your Cadette team','and reflect on your efforts and their impact. Take some time and talk it through. What will you do differently the next time you decide to act for Earth?
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30013,300133);
INSERT into Requirements(300134,'Affirm your commitment','to strive to be an heir apparent of air and all of Planet Earth\'s elements.
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30013,300134);
INSERT into Quests(30014,'Leader in Action');
INSERT into JourneysHasQuests(3001,30014);
INSERT into Requirements(300141,'Identify a team of Brownies','on (or about to be on) their WOW! Wonders of Water journey. Or find a team that recently completed WOW!
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30014,300141);
INSERT into Requirements(300142,'Talk to the volunteer','\"guiding the Brownies and find out what the team is doing; what the Brownies enjoy; and what the volunteer finds challenging. Take a look at the Brownie WOW! Book and flip through the adult book; too! Now the fun begins!\"
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30014,300142);
INSERT into Requirements(300143,'Arrange to be at some of the ','Brownie Team\'s gatherings; coordinating the schedule with the volunteers so you\'ll have time to do each of these:
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30014,300143);
INSERT into Requirements(300144,'Guide the Brownies','\"through a fun activity that teaches them something about Earth\'s air or water or both! You can adapt an activity from your journey for younger girls; check out some of the options in the WOW! Girls\' book and volunteer books; or create an activity of your own. A magical science experiment? Making rainbows? Making and flying a kite? Enjoy the sounds of nature? Scanty stuff? A game you invent about animals that inhabit water and sky? Or perhaps you and some friends can act out a scene from \"\"A Very Wet ELF Adventure\"\" or even make a short puppet show based on the story. Better yet; guide the Brownies to do their own!\"
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30014,300144);
INSERT into Requirements(300145,'Inspire the Brownies','to try a new healthy habit--a watery treat (check out the ideas in the WOW! book); some fun cardio or yoga exercises; or a fruit or veggie grown with local water (and air!). Check with the Brownie\'s volunteer about food allergies before you plan any snacks. Your goal is to get the Brownies thinking about how what is good for us is often good for Earth; too!
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30014,300145);
INSERT into Requirements(300146,'Engage the Brownies','in a short activity that gets them thinking about what great teamwork looks like. Maybe you know a game or maybe you can invent one that gets the Brownies cooperating. If not; get some ideas from other Girl Scouts in your area. Teac the game as an opening or closing or an energizing break. While the Brownies are exploring the Wonders of Water; they are also practicing another WOW--Ways of Working. Your goal is to get the Brownies practicing some really great WOWs!
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30014,300146);
INSERT into Requirements(300147,'Share with the Brownies','a line from the Girl Scout Law that you are trying to live out in your life right now. Tell them what you are doing to bring that line to life. Then; ask them to tell you about a line they are living out!
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30014,300147);
INSERT into Requirements(300148,'After you\'ve completed','your mission with the Brownies; ask the volunteer for input on what you did. What was great? What might you want to do a little differently in the future?
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30014,300148);
INSERT into Requirements(300149,'Now that you\'ve enjoyed some time','\"inspiring Brownies; think about and answer these question:·What did you Discover within yourself as you guided Brownies?·Why is it important to Connect with younger girls?·What did you accomplish on behalf of the Earth by Taking Action to educate and inspire Brownies?\"
INSERT into QuestHasRequirements(30014,300149);
